```graphql
# Schema definition:
type Query {
  user(id: ID!): User
  users(limit: Int = 10): [User!]!
}

# Client query:
query GetUser($id: ID!) {
  user(id: $id) {
    name
    email
    posts { title }
  }
}
```
**Query** is the read-only entry point. Variables prefixed with `$` are passed separately from the query.

```graphql
mutation CreateUser($input: CreateUserInput!) {
  createUser(input: $input) {
    id
    name
  }
}

# Variables:
# { "input": { "name": "John", "email": "john@example.com" } }
```
**Mutation** modifies server data. Use input types for complex arguments. Returns the modified data.

```graphql
fragment UserFields on User {
  id
  name
  email
}

query {
  user(id: "1") { ...UserFields }
  admin: user(id: "2") { ...UserFields }
}
```
**fragment** avoids field duplication. Spread with `...FragmentName`. Inline fragments: `... on Type { }`.
